Python Basics – List and Dictionary

Overview

This folder contains Python programs that demonstrate how to use lists and dictionaries — two of the most important data structures in Python.
These examples are designed for beginners to understand data storage, manipulation, and retrieval using simple and practical examples.

⸻

Topics Covered

Lists
	•	Creating and accessing list elements
	•	Adding, removing, and updating items
	•	Looping through lists
	•	Common list methods: append(), insert(), pop(), remove(), sort(), etc.

Dictionaries
	•	Creating key–value pairs
	•	Accessing and updating dictionary values
	•	Looping through keys and values
	•	Dictionary methods: items(), keys(), values()
	•	Nested dictionaries

Combined Usage
	•	Using lists inside dictionaries and dictionaries inside lists
	•	Real-world examples such as storing and organizing student or product data

⸻

Objective

The goal of this folder is to:
	•	Build a strong foundation in list and dictionary operations
	•	Show how to combine both structures for real-life applications
	•	Prepare for advanced data manipulation in Python such as working with JSON or APIs
